'Nill','2013-04-01 01:53:23.743181'),('http://www.cs.sfu.ca/%7Efedorova','Dr. Alexandra Fedorova, SFU School of Computing Science','<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC \"-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN\" \"http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd\">\n\n<html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">\n<head>\n<title>Dr. Alexandra Fedorova, SFU School of Computing Science</title>\n<meta content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\" http-equiv=\"Content-Type\"/>\n<link href=\"style.css\" rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\"/>\n</head>\n<body>\n<div id=\"wrapper\">\n<h1>Alexandra Fedorova</h1>\n<ul id=\"nav\">\n<li><a href=\"research.html\"></a></li>\n<li class=\"a\"><a href=\"research.html\">Research</a></li>\n<li class=\"d\"><a href=\"teaching.html\">Teaching</a></li>\n<li class=\"c\"><a href=\"publications.html\">Publications</a></li>\n<li class=\"a\"><a href=\"cv.pdf\">CV</a></li>\n</ul>\n<div id=\"body\">\n<div><div><div><div class=\"inner\">\n<img alt=\"My photo\" class=\"left\" height=\"160\" src=\"images/face-tom.jpg\" width=\"240\"/>\n<div class=\"indent\">\n<div class=\"main\">\n<h2><b>Dr. Alexandra Fedorova</b></h2>\n<b>Associate Professor</b>\n<br><b>School of Computing Science, SFU</b>\n<br><b> <i>Sloan Research Fellow</i></b>\n<br><b>Consultant, <a href=\"http://www.wiredtiger.com\">WiredTiger</a></b>\n<p>Check out <a href=\"http://totally-drive-certified.blogspot.ca\">my\n				blog</a>\n<p>\n<b>Quick facts:</b> I am a co-leader of the <a href=\"http://synar.cs.sfu.ca/systems-research.html\">Systems Research Group</a>, with Arrvindh Shriraman, and a co-founder of the <a href=\"http://synar.cs.sfu.ca\">SyNAr </a> (Systems, Networking and Architecture) lab. Research focus is on system design for multicore processors and\n			      parallel computing. \n\n<p>I had the honour of working on my PhD <a href=\"http://www.cs.sfu.ca/~fedorova/thesis.pdf\">thesis</a> in Computer Science\n			 <a href=\"http://www.eecs.harvard.edu\">at Harvard\n			 </a> (graduated 2006) under the supervision of\n			 a great person, scientist and entrepreneur     <a href=\"http://www.eecs.harvard.edu/~margo\">Margo	Seltzer</a> and with other great folks like Chris Small, Mike Smith, Mark Moir and his Scalable Synchronization team at Sun (now Oracle).\n\n	\n	      \n<p>Huge thanks to Oracle (formerly Sun Microsystems), National Science and\n			Engineering Research Council of Canada (NSERC),\n			STMicroelectronics, Google, Research in Motion,\n			    Electronic Arts BlackBox, and\n			Intel for supporting our research.\n\n<p>If you are a prospective student or postdoc interested in joining my group, <a href=\"http://synar.cs.sfu.ca/potential-applicants.html\">read this info page</a>.\n<p>\nIf you are a prospective employer, contact me -- I am fortunate to be\n				      working with a team of highly\n				      talented and motivated students.\n<p>\n<h2>News</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>I am on sabbatical in 2013-2014. Very excited to be working for <a href=\"http://www.wiredtiger.com\">WiredTiger</a>.</li>\n<li>I am looking for a post-doc to begin September, 2013. Kernel hacking\n					experience or the ability to\n					quickly acquire it is\n					important. Send me your CV if\n					interested. </li>\n<li>Our work on memory management on NUMA systems will appear in ASPLOS 2013</li>\n<li>Many thanks to the Sloan foundation for their 2012 <a href=\"http://www.sloan.org/assets/files/press_releases/2012_srf_press_release_vf.pdf\">Sloan Fellowship</a>.</li>\n<li>Many thanks to ACM/CRA-W for the 2011 <a href=\"http://cra-w.org/ArticleDetails/tabid/77/ArticleID/161/Default.aspx\">Anita Borg Early Career Award</a>. Award\n				presentation video at USENIX is <a href=\"http://www.usenix.org/events/atc11/stream/opening/index.html\">here</a>.\n<li>SFU is <a href=\"http://oncampus.macleans.ca/education/2012/11/01/2013-comprehensive\">ranked #1 again</a> among Canada\'s comprehensive universities -- a position it has held ten times since the rankings began 20 years agomore than any other university. It is also the third year in a row that SFU has perched on top. Furthermore, HESA ranked SFU among <a href=\"http://www.sfu.ca/sfunews/stories/2012/sfu-a-top-10-research-university.html\">top 10 research universities in Canada</a>. </li>\n</li></ul>\n<h2>Professional Activities:</h2>\n<ul>\n<li> <b>Techincal Program committees:</b> HotOS 2013, HotPar 2012, USENIX 2012, VEE 2012, ASPLOS 2012, HotPar 2011, USENIX 2011, EuroSys 2011, PPoPP 2011,\n				HiPEAC 2011, PACT 2010, HotPar 2010, EuroSys 2010, PESPMA 2009-2010,\n				ASPLOS 2009, HotPar\n				2009, ACM Operating Systems Review 2009\n				(Special Issue on the Interaction among the\n				OS, Compilers and Multicore Processors),\n				WIOSCA 2007-2010, MMCS 2008-2010, SPAA 2008. </li>\n<li> <b>Chairing activities: </b>Chair of Provocative\n				Ideas Session at ASPLOS 2012, Program committee co-chair, HotPar 2009 (with Jim\n				Larus) </li>\n<li> <b>Other conference organization: </b>HotPar Steering Committee, Local\n				Arrangements Chair for High Performance\n				Graphics 2011 (HPG\'11)</li>\n</ul>\n</p></p></p></p></p></p></p></br></br></br></div>\n</div>\n<div id=\"dividerx\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"12\" src=\"images/divider_cut.gif\" width=\"28\"/></div>\n<div id=\"boxes\">\n<div><div class=\"inner\">\n<div id=\"left\"><div class=\"inner\">\n<h2>Contact Information:</h2>\n<p>Dr. Alexandra Fedorova<br>\n                          School of Computing Science<br>\n                          8888 University Drive <br>\n                          Burnaby, BC V5A 1S6, <br>\n                          Canada<br><br>\n                          Phone: +1 (778) 782-6904 <br>\n                          Fax: +1 (778)782-3045 <br>\n						  E-mail: fedorova@cs.sfu.ca <br>\n</br></br></br></br></br></br></br></br></br></p></div></div><!-- end left -->\n<div id=\"right\"><div class=\"inner\">\n<table><tr>\n<td valign=\"top\">\n<h2>Students and Postdocs</h2>\n<ul class=\"left\">\n<li>Micah Best (co-supervised PhD) </li>\n<li> <a href=\"http://www.cs.sfu.ca/~sba70/personal/\">Sergey Blagodurov</a> (PhD) </li>\n<li> Mohammad\n				      Dashti (PhD) </li>\n<li> <a href=\"http://www.sfu.ca/~jfunston\">Justin Funston</a> (PhD) </li>\n<li> Fabien Gaud (Postdoc) </li>\n<li> Jessica Jiang (MSc)</li>\n<li> Craig\n				Mustard (PhD) </li>\n<li>Svetozar Miucin (PhD) </li>\n<li>Karol Swietlicki (BSc) </li>\n<li> Evgeny Vinnik (PhD) </li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"50%\">\n<h2>Alumni (first job)</h2>\n<ul class=\"left\">\n<li><a href=\"http://www.sfu.ca/~tdwyer\">Tyler Dwyer</a>, MSc </li>\n<li>Mark Roth, MSc (Microsoft) </li>\n<li> Ananth Narayan S., MSc (Intel) </li>\n<li> Shane Mottishaw, MSc (Corensic)</li>\n<li> <a href=\"http://www.cs.sfu.ca/~sza21/personal/\">Sergey Zhuravlev</a>, MSc (Teradici) </li>\n<li> Juan Carlos\n				      Saez, co-supervised PhD (Complutense\n				      University, Madrid) </li>\n<li>Viren Kuman, MSc (SAP)</li>\n<li>Vahid Kazempour, MSc (<a href=\"http://www.quic.com\">\n				       QuIC Financial</a>)</li>\n<li>Ali Kamali, MSc (<a href=\"\n					http://www.avigilon.com/\">Avigilon</a>) </li>\n<li> Nasser Ghazali-Beiklar, MSc (InfoMine) </li>\n</ul>\n</td></tr></table>\n</div></div><!-- end right -->\n<div class=\"clear\"></div>\n</div></div>\n</div><!-- end boxes -->\n</div></div></div></div><!-- end .inner -->\n</div><!-- end body -->\n<div id=\"footer\">\n</div><!-- end footer -->\n</div><!-- end wrapper -->\n</body>\n</html>\n','2013-04-01 02:02:54.721069'),('http://www.cs.sfu.ca/about/school-facilities/course-mail-list.html','Course Mail List FAQ - Computing Science - Simon Fraser University','\n<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC \"-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN\"  \"http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd\">\n\n<html>\n<head>\n<meta content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\" http-equiv=\"content-type\"/>\n<meta content=\"\" http-equiv=\"keywords\"/>\n<title>\n        Course Mail List FAQ\n         - Computing Science\n        - Simon Fraser University\