><a href=\"#7\">Whom should I contact about e-mail problems with my account?</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#8\">Who can send to a course list?</a></li>\n</ul>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text \">\n<h2><a name=\"1\"></a>Which courses have e-mail lists?</h2>\n<p>Every CMPT course taught during the current semester has a corresponding e-mail list on the sfu.ca domain.</p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text \">\n<h2><a name=\"2\"></a>How are the lists named?</h2>\n<p>The name of an e-mail list is <b><i>cmpt-xxx@sfu.ca</i></b>, where \'<b><i>xxx</i></b>\' is the course number. CMPT 354, for example, has the list name <b><i>cmpt-354</i> AT <i>sfu</i> DOT <i>ca</i>.</b></p>\n<p>In the case of multiple sections, <b>-d1, -d2, -e1, -c1</b>, etc. is added to the name as appropriate. e.g. <b><i>cmpt-101-d1</i> AT  <i>sfu</i> DOT <i>ca</i>, <i>cmpt-101-d2</i> AT <i>sfu</i> DOT <i>ca</i>. </b></p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text \">\n<h2><a name=\"3\"></a>Which Unix accounts are added to the lists?</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>The course instructor</li>\n<li>The course teaching assistant(s)</li>\n<li>Registered students</li>\n<li>Special requests from the instructor</li>\n</ul>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text \">\n<h2><a name=\"4\"></a>When are registered students added and dropped?</h2>\n<p>E-mail lists are automatically updated daily, according to information obtained from the Registrar\'s Office. Accounts are automatically e-mailed when they have been added or dropped from a course list.</p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text \">\n<h2><a name=\"5\"></a>How do I find out if I am on an e-mail list?</h2>\n<p>Log on to your SFU <a href=\"https://my.sfu.ca/cgi-bin/WebObjects/manage.woa\">Account Management</a> web page to check and manage your mail list memberships.</p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text \">\n<h2><a name=\"6\"></a>How do I contact my Instructor(s) and/or TA(s)?</h2>\n<p>Send an e-mail message to <b><i>cmpt-xxx-help </i>AT<i> sfu </i>DOT<i> ca</i></b>, where \'xxx\' is your course number. For example, to contact your instructor(s) and TA(s) for CMPT-125-d2, send your email to: <b><i>cmpt-125-d2-help </i>AT<i> sfu </i>DOT<i> ca</i></b>.</p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text \">\n<h2><a name=\"7\"></a>Whom should I contact about e-mail problems with my account?</h2>\n<p>Please <a href=\"/about/school-facilities/how-to-contact-helpdesk.html\">e-mail helpdesk</a>. In some cases the problem must be handled by SFU technical support (help AT sfu DOT ca), but helpdesk AT cs DOT sfu DOT ca will forward it to them if necessary.</p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text \">\n<h2><a name=\"8\"></a>Who can send to a course list?</h2>\n<p>For CMPT courses, only instructors and TAs can send to the course mail list.</p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text \">\n<hr>\n<p>For more information, please click <a href=\"http://www.sfu.ca/itservices/sfuconnect/email/maillistsetup.html\">here</a>.<br>\n</br></p>\n</hr></div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div id=\"sub_content_wrapper\">\n<div class=\"parsys aboveSubContent\"><div class=\"parbase section reference\"><div class=\"cq-dd-paragraph\"><div class=\"searchwidget\">\n<div class=\"\">\n<p>Search Computing Science</p>\n<form action=\"/search.html\" method=\"get\">\n<input name=\"q\" placeholder=\"\"/>\n<input class=\"submit\" type=\"submit\" value=\"Search\"/>\n</form>\n</div></div>\n</div></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"parsys sub_content\"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div id=\"footer\">\n<ul>\n<li>8888 University Drive, Burnaby, B.C. Canada V5A 1S6</li>\n<li><a href=\"//www.sfu.ca/webmaster/terms.html\">Terms / Privacy</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"//www.sfu.ca/contact/index.html\">Contact SFU</a></li