ourse-mail-list.html\">Course Mail List FAQ</a></li><li><a href=\"/about/school-facilities/access-card.html\">Card Access FAQ</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li><li><a href=\"/about/history.html\">History of the School</a></li><li><a href=\"/about/job-opportunities.html\">Job Opportunities</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li><li><a href=\"/undergraduate.html\">Undergraduate Students</a></li><li><a href=\"/graduateprogram.html\">Graduate Students</a></li><li><a href=\"/research.html\">Research</a></li><li><a href=\"/industryrelations.html\">Industry Relations</a></li><li><a href=\"/people.html\">People</a></li><li><a href=\"/newsandevents.html\">News &amp; Events</a></li><li class=\"rule\">Â </li><li><a href=\"https://intraweb.cs.sfu.ca/\">Intranet</a></li><li><a href=\"https://portal.cs.sfu.ca/\">Portal</a></li>\n</ul><ul><li class=\"rule\">Â </li></ul><div class=\"parsys contentBelow\"><div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text \">\n<p>Â  FOLLOW AND SHARE</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.facebook.com/FAS.SFU\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"/content/dam/sfu/images/icons/facebook_32.png\"/></a> <a href=\"https://twitter.com/#!/FAS_SFU\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"/content/dam/sfu/images/icons/twitter_32.png\"/></a> <a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/fas_sfu\" target=\"_blank\"><img height=\"35\" src=\"/content/dam/sfu/images/icons/flickr.png\" width=\"35\"/></a> <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/fascomms\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"/content/dam/sfu/images/icons/youtube-icon_32x32.png\"/></a></p>\n</div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div id=\"content_2col\">\n<div class=\"breadcrumb\">\n<a href=\"/computing.html\">Computing Science</a>Â &gt;Â <a href=\"/about.html\">About Computing Science</a>Â &gt;Â <a href=\"/about/school-facilities.html\">School Facilities</a>Â &gt;Â <a href=\"/about/school-facilities/how-to-print-photocopy-and-scan.html\">How to print, photocopy and scan</a></div>\n<div id=\"main_content_wrapper\">\n<div class=\"parsys main_content\"><div class=\"title section\"><div><h1>How to print, photocopy and scan</h1></div></div>\n<div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text \">\n<h2>Overview</h2>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text \">\n<p>To best serve our faculty, staff and graduate students, there are many documentation related services provided by Faculty of Applied Science and the School of Computing Science.<br>\n<br>\nThis page gives some tips and guidelines on how to get the documentation jobs done with ease.<br>\n</br></br></br></p>\n<p>For printing in CSIL, please visit this <a href=\"/about/school-facilities/csil/how-to-print.html\">page</a>.<br>\n<br>\n<b><i><u>This page is still under construction. But we could not delay the publishing due to the tremendous value of the information on this page. Please help us to enrich this page.</u></i></b></br></br></p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text \">\n<h2>Table of Contents<br>\n</br></h2>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text \">\n<h4>Essentials<br>\n</br></h4>\n<p><a href=\"#basic-tips\">Basic tips of printing and photocopying</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"#basic-print\">How to print?</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"#basic-photocopy\">How to photocopy?</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"#basic-scan\">How to scan paper/photos?</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"#large-numbers\">I want to make hundreds of paper handouts, can someone help me?</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"/about/school-facilities/how-to-print-photocopy-and-scan.html#order-supplies\">The printer I am using is running out of suppliies, how to get more?</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"#recycle\">I have collected a few used ink/toner cartridges, what I should do with them?</a></p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text \">\n<h4>About printing<br>\n</br></h4>\n<p><a href=\"#faculty-print\">Which printers are available for faculty members?</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"#staff-print\">Which printers are available for staff?</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"#new-grad-print\">How to print as a new CMPT graduate student?</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"#research-lab-print\">How to print from a research lab computer?</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"#add-printer-windows\">How to add a FASnet printer to my Windows 7 system?</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"#add-printer-windowsxp\">How to add a FASnet printer to my Windows XP system?</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"#print-poster\">I would like to print a oversized poster, what I should do?</a></p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text \">\n<h4>Special topics on printing</h4>\n<p><a href=\"#visitor-print\">Which printers are available for visitors?</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"#wireless-print\">I\'m using a laptop, which printers I could use?</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"#print-to-mfd\">May I print to the new Multi-Function Devices?</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"#print-use-printcard\">May I print to ITS printers using SFU printing cards?</a></p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text \">\n<h4>About using Konica/Minolta Multi-Function Devices<br>\n</br></h4>\n<p><a href=\"#km-copy\">How to make a copy</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"#km-scan\">How to scan to an email account</a><br>\n</br></p>\n<p><a href=\"#km-transparency\">How to photocopy to overhead transparencies</a><br>\n</br></p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text \">\n<h4>Known issues</h4>\n<p><a href=\"#issue-no-color\">I don\'t get color printout while I print to a color printer; what I should do?</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"#issue-multi-page-per-sheet\">I print multiple copies but only got one copy; what I should do?</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"#issue-duplex\">I print a single page, but it shows the job has 2 pages; what I should do?</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"#issue-sims\">I have trouble printing within SIMS; what I should do?</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"#issue-papersize\">I print from a Windows computer but the printout is shifted somehow; what I should do?</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"#issue-filesize\">I scaned a lot of pages on the MFD and sent to my SFU Connect email address, but I did not get the scanned file nor got any error message; what happened?</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"#issue-sliceoff-mac\">I print from a Mac computer but the printout is sliced-off somehow; what I should do?</a></p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text \">\n<hr>\n<h4>Essentials</h4>\n</hr></div></div>\n<div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text \">\n<h2><a name=\"basic-tips\"></a>Basic tips of printing and photocopying<br>\n</br></h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Always use <b>letter</b> size paper<ul>\n<li>To print to other paper sizes, please make sure there is stack of proper size of paper in the paper tray or at manual feed port.<br>\n</br></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Please print double-sided for drafts and other informal occasions.</li>\n<li>Please print to Black&amp;White printers when no color printout is needed.<ul>\n<li>save some money, save some green.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>If the number of handouts is large, please contact the receptionist to get the printouts more economically.</li>\n<li>Before printing to transparency, make sure the transparency is the correct type for the printer and no one else is using the printer. Use manual feed is recommended.<br>\n</br></li>\n<li>(Recommended) Use electronic files when possible. Generating PDF files is free :)</li>\n<li>Throughout the SFU community, it is recommended to use enterprise level devices for best manageability and reliability with minimum cost.</li>\n<li>Read through this page for more useful tips.</li>\n</ul>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text \">\n<h2><a name=\"basic-print\"></a>How to print?</h2>\n<p>For UNIX/Linux hosts, please select a printer from the list.<br>\n</br></p>\n<p>For Windows hosts, in general, please use print server <b>printserv1.fas.sfu.ca</b>.</p>\n<p>If there are issues with this <b>printserv1</b>, please <a href=\"/about/school-facilities/how-to-contact-helpdesk.html\">report to helpdesk</a> asap. The <i>rcg-fs1.rcg.sfu.ca</i> is a temporary alternative if printserv1 stopped working suddenly.<br>\n</br></p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text \">\n<h2><a name=\"basic-photocopy\"></a>How to photocopy?</h2>\n<p>There are a few Konica/Minolta Multi-Function-Devices around:</p>\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td>device id</td>\n<td>location</td>\n<td>feature</td>\n<td>user</td>\n<td>remarks</td>\n</tr><tr><td>Â </td>\n<td>TASC1 9201</td>\n<td>color</td>\n<td>faculty, staff<br>\n</br></td>\n<td>Â </td>\n</tr><tr><td>Â </td>\n<td>TASC1 9217</td>\n<td>black &amp; white</td>\n<td>grads, faculty<br>\n</br></td>\n<td>Â </td>\n</tr><tr><td>Â </td>\n<td>ASB 9971 mailroom<br>\n</br></td>\n<td>black &amp; white</td>\n<td>staff, faculty</td>\n<td>Â </td>\n</tr><tr><td>Â </td>\n<td>Surrey\n</td>\n<td>Â </td>\n<td>Â </td>\n<td>Â </td>\n</tr></tbody></table>\n<p>You need to key in the copier code to authenticate and manage the funds.</p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text \">\n<h2><a name=\"basic-scan\"></a>How to scan paper/photos?</h2>\n<p>All of the Konica/Minolta Multi-Function Devices are capable of scanning. Please scan it to your SFU Connect email.</p>\n<p>In general, please <b>do not reply</b> to the message generated from the scanner/MFD. When there are some issues with the scanning, please do reply the message with the details of the issues.<br>\n</br></p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text \">\n<h2><a name=\"large-numbers\"></a>I want to make hundreds of paper handouts, can someone help me?</h2>\n<p>If you have to make large number of pages printed on paper, please contact CS receptionist in advance to get the material published.</p>\n<p>Printing or photocopying is not recommended.</p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text \">\n<h2><a name=\"order-supplies\"></a>The printer I am using is running out of suppliies, how to get more?<br>\n</br></h2>\n<p>Please <a href=\"/about/school-facilities/how-to-contact-helpdesk.html\">email helpdesk</a> with the details of the supplies.</p>\n<p>Special note: if this is a research lab printer or a personal printer, before the order could be put through, we must receive <i><u>an email confirmation of the purchase from a faculty member includes an account number</u></i> which will be covering the cost of the supplies.<br>\n</br></p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text \">\n<h2><a name=\"recycle\"></a>I have collected a few used ink/toner cartridges, what I should do with them?<br>\n</br></h2>\n<p>Please <a href=\"/about/school-facilities/how-to-contact-helpdesk.html\">email helpdesk</a> so we could come and collect them.</p>\n<p>SFU has a recycle program and recycle used cartridges is part of it.</p>\n<p>Please handle the cartridges with care - the dust is harmful!</p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text \">\n<hr>\n<h4>About printing</h4>\n</hr></div></div>\n<div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text \">\n<h2><a name=\"faculty-print\"></a>Which printers are available for faculty members?</h2>\n<p>Here is the list of the printers for faculty; they should only be accessed through the ITS\' print server.<br>\n</br></p>\n<h3>Burnaby Campus<br>\n</br></h3>\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td>printer name</td>\n<td>location</td>\n<td>feature</td>\n<td>printer name for Windows client</td>\n</tr><tr><td>cmpt-t9201</td>\n<td>TASC1 9201</td>\n<td>Black &amp; White</td>\n<td>\\\\printserv1.fas.sfu.ca\\cmpt-t9201</td>\n</tr><tr><td>cmpt-prism</td>\n<td>TASC1 9201</td>\n<td>Color</td>\n<td>\\\\printserv1.fas.sfu.ca\\cmpt-prism</td>\n</tr><tr><td>cmpt-faculty</td>\n<td>TASC1 8003</td>\n<td>Black &amp; White</td>\n<td>\\\\printserv1.fas.sfu.ca\\cmpt-faculty</td>\n</tr><tr><td>cmpt-pigment</td>\n<td>TASC1 8003</td>\n<td>Color</td>\n<td>\\\\printserv1.fas.sfu.ca\\cmpt-pigment</td>\n</tr><tr><td>cmpt-mailroom</td>\n<td>ASB 9971 mailroom</td>\n<td>black &amp; white</td>\n<td>\\\\printserv1.fas.sfu.ca\\cmpt-mailroom</td>\n</tr></tbody></table>\n<p>Â </p>\n<p>You may also use the printers in the grad open lab (using the printing cards and release station). See <a href=\"#new-grad-print\">this Q&amp;A</a> for details.</p>\n<p>For the directors of research labs, you may use the <a href=\"#research-lab-print\">lab printer</a>(s).</p>\n<h3>Surrey Campus</h3>\n<p>(...)</p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text \">\n<h2><a name=\"staff-print\"></a>Which printers are available for staff?</h2>\n<p>The helpdesk will configure all the printers for each staff personally.<br>\n</br></p>\n<h3>Burnaby Campus</h3>\n<p>Here is just a list of the printers CMPT staff could use; they should only be accessed through the ITS\' print server.<br>\n</br></p>\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td>printer name</td>\n<td>location</td>\n<td>feature</td>\n<td>printer name for Windows client</td>\n</tr><tr><td>cmpt-mailroom</td>\n<td>ASB 9971 mailroom</td>\n<td>black &amp; white</td>\n<td>\\\\printserv1.fas.sfu.ca\\cmpt-mailroom</td>\n</tr><tr><td>cmpt-office</td>\n<td>outside ASB9971.5</td>\n<td>black &amp; white</td>\n<td>\\\\printserv1.fas.sfu.ca\\cmpt-office</td>\n</tr><tr><td>cmpt-t9201</td>\n<td>TASC1 9201</td>\n<td>Black &amp; White</td>\n<td>\\\\printserv1.fas.sfu.ca\\cmpt-t9201</td>\n</tr><tr><td>cmpt-prism</td>\n<td>TASC1 9201</td>\n<td>Color</td>\n<td>\\\\printserv1.fas.sfu.ca\\cmpt-prism</td>\n</tr><tr><td>cmpt-faculty</td>\n<td>TASC1 8003</td>\n<td>Black &amp; White</td>\n<td>\\\\printserv1.fas.sfu.ca\\cmpt-faculty</td>\n</tr><tr><td>cmpt-pigment</td>\n<td>TASC1 8003</td>\n<td>Color</td>\n<td>\\\\printserv1.fas.sfu.ca\\cmpt-pigment</td>\n</tr></tbody></table>\n<p>Â </p>\n<h3>Surrey Campus</h3>\n<p>(...)<br>\n</br></p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text \">\n<h2><a name=\"new-grad-print\"></a>How to print as a new CMPT graduate student?</h2>\n<p>When joining the School of Computing Science, the graduate students have access to the graduate student open lab (TASC1 9217 and SRY 4122).</p>\n<h3>Burnaby Campus</h3>\n<p>In TASC1 9217, you should be able to print to <b>DCF_BnW</b> and <b>DCF_Color</b> and release it from the release station in the same room and get printouts in the same room. You may want to check out <a href=\"/about/school-facilities/csil/how-to-print.html\">this page</a> for more details.<br>\n</br></p>\n<h3>Surrey Campus</h3>\n<p>In SRY 4122, you could do the following: (to be answered)</p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text \">\n<h2><a name=\"research-lab-print\"></a>How to print from a research lab computer?</h2>\n<p>In general, there is at least one printer in each research lab shared by all the users in this specific lab.<br>\n</br></p>\n<h3>Burnaby campus</h3>\n<p>For a Windows workstation, it is recommended to use the server <b>printserv1.fas.sfu.ca</b>. TheÂ <i>rcg-fs1.rcg.sfu.ca</i> is a temporary alternative if printserv1 stopped working.<br>\n</br></p>\n<p>Here is the list of the printers:</p>\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td>printer name</td>\n<td>location</td>\n<td>user</td>\n<td>remarks</td>\n</tr><tr><td>cmpt-nml</td>\n<td>TASC1 9002<br>\n</br></td>\n<td>NML</td>\n<td>Â </td>\n</tr><tr><td>cmpt-nml0</td>\n<td>TASC1 9002</td>\n<td>NML</td>\n<td>Â </td>\n</tr><tr><td>computational-logic</td>\n<td>TASC1 9000</td>\n<td>CLL</td>\n<td>Â </td>\n</tr><tr><td>cstheory1</td>\n<td>TASC1 9001</td>\n<td>ATL</td>\n<td>Â </td>\n</tr><tr><td>cstheory2</td>\n<td>TASC1 8208</td>\n<td>ATL</td>\n<td>Â </td>\n</tr><tr><td>dbprinter</td>\n<td>TASC1 9006</td>\n<td>DBL</td>\n<td>Â </td>\n</tr><tr><td>hollerith</td>\n<td>TASC1 8004<br>\n</br></td>\n<td>GrUVi<br>\n</br></td>\n<td>Â </td>\n</tr><tr><td>jian-printer</td>\n<td>TASC1 9406</td>\n<td>DBL</td>\n<td>Â </td>\n</tr><tr><td>ming-printer</td>\n<td>TASC1 9406</td>\n<td>DBL</td>\n<td>Â </td>\n</tr><tr><td>mellow</td>\n<td>TASC1 9400</td>\n<td>MIAL</td>\n<td>Â </td>\n</tr><tr><td>nlpr</td>\n<td>TASC1 9404<br>\n</br></td>\n<td>NLL</td>\n<td>Â </td>\n</tr><tr><td>orange</td>\n<td>TASC1 9406</td>\n<td>Â </td>\n<td>Â </td>\n</tr><tr><td>vision</td>\n<td>TASC1 8005</td>\n<td>CVL</td>\n<td>Â </td>\n</tr></tbody></table>\n<p>Â </p>\n<p>About Windows workstations: please ask the lab admin to get the printer drivers added to the Windows system, and then you could add the printer(s) to your own profile.</p>\n<h3>Surrey campus</h3>\n<p>...</p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text \">\n<h2><a name=\"add-printer-windows\"></a>How to add a FASnet printer to my Windows 7 system?<br>\n</br></h2>\n<p>First of all, if you are not the administrator of the computer, you may need to contact helpdesk (or lab admin if you are using a research lab computer) to get proper driver installed in advance. But the administrator could not a printer to your printer list for you.<br>\n</br></p>\n<p>Once the printer driver has been installed on the system, you may do the following:<br>\n</br></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Logon to the Windows system as usual</li>\n<li>Click Windows Start icon, select \"Devices and Printers\"<br>\n</br></li>\n<li>Within the newly opened window, under \"Printers and Faxes\" section, right click on the blank space and select \"Add printer\" of the popup menu.</li>\n<li>Within the newly opened \"Add Printer\" dialog box, click \"Add a network, wireless or Bluetooth printer\"<br>\n</br></li>\n<li>Click \"The printer that I want isn\'t listed\"<br>\n</br></li>\n<li>Key in the partial path to a printer on a print server (e.g. \"<b>\\\\printserv1.fas.sfu.ca\\</b>\") under \"Select a shared printer by name\"; please note: all the back-slashes must be used as instructed here.<br>\n</br></li>\n<li>Now, you will see bunch of printers listed; pick the one you\'d like to use.</li>\n<li>Click \"Next\" button and watch the installation finishes.</li>\n<li>Please do not set it to your default printer - the default printer should always be a pseudo PDF printer.</li>\n<li>Please select \"do NOT share this printer\" when prompted.</li>\n<li>Click OK a few times and done.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>This will add one printer to your profile; if you want have other printers added to your fleet, please repeat these steps.</p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text \">\n<h2><a name=\"add-printer-windowsxp\"></a>How to add a FASnet printer to my Windows XP system?<br>\n</br></h2>\n<p>First of all, if you are not the administrator of the computer, you may need to contact helpdesk (or lab admin if you are using a research lab computer) to get proper driver installed in advance. But the administrator could not a printer to your printer list for you.<br>\n</br></p>\n<p>Once the printer driver has been installed on the system, you may do the following:<br>\n</br></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Logon to the Windows system as usual</li>\n<li>Click Windows Start icon, select \"Printers and Faxes\" from the menu<br>\n</br></li>\n<li>Within the newly opened window, right click on the blank space and select \"Add printer\" of the popup menu.</li>\n<li>click \"Next\" button</li>\n<li>Within the newly opened \"Add Printer Wizard\" dialog box, check \"Add a network printer, or a printer attached to another computer\", click \"Next\" button<br>\n</br></li>\n<li>Check the radio button \"Connect to this printer (or to browse for a printer, select this option and ...)\"</li>\n<li>Click the text field next to \"Name\", key in the partial path to a printer on a print server (e.g. \"<b>\\\\printserv1.fas.sfu.ca\\</b>\") <br>\n<ul>\n<li>please note: all the back-slashes must be used as instructed here.<br>\n</br></li>\n</ul>\n</br></li>\n<li>Now, you will see bunch of printers listed; pick the one you\'d like to use.</li>\n<li>Click \"Next\" button and watch the installation finishes.</li>\n<li>Please do not set it to your default printer - the default printer should always be a pseudo PDF printer.</li>\n<li>Please select \"do NOT share this printer\" when prompted.</li>\n<li>Click OK a few times and done.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>This will add one printer to your profile; if you want have other printers added to your fleet, please repeat these steps.</p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text \">\n<h2><a name=\"print-poster\"></a>I would like to print a oversized poster, what I should do?</h2>\n<p>The School do not have the equipment to handle oversized printing. Here are two places you may look on/near Burnaby Campus:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>The SFU\'s <a href=\"http://www.sfu.ca/docsol\">Document Solutions</a> could do this and they will do a good job.</li>\n<li>The independent <a href=\"www.printcornerstone.com\">print/copy shop in Cornerstone building</a> offer services as well. Please ensure you are satisfied with the quality (check out their samples) before placing your order.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Please note: there are costs involved.<br>\n</br></p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text \">\n<hr>\n<h4>Special topics on printing<br>\n</br></h4>\n</hr></div></div>\n<div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text \">\n<h2><a name=\"visitor-print\"></a>Which printers are available for visitors?</h2>\n<p>Generally speaking, there are some scenarios:<br>\n</br></p>\n<p style=\"margin-left: 40px;\"><br>\nA) You could print to printer cmpt-t9201.cs.sfu.ca through TCP/IP directly from your laptop (on wireless network).<br>\n<br>\nB). There are USB cables near the printers in TASC1-9201; you could directly hook up the cable between the printer and your laptop, you should be able to print (after you get the printer driver installed).<br>\n<br>\nC). You could use \"Remote Desktop Connections\" connect to ts.fas.sfu.ca (using account fas.sfu.ca\\csguest?). From this terminal server, you could add printers <a>\\\\printserv1.fas.sfu.ca\\cmpt-t9201</a> and <a>\\\\printserv1.fas.sfu.ca\\cmpt-prism</a>. Then you could print to these printers.<br>\n</br></br></br></br></br></br></p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text \">\n<h2><a name=\"print-to-mfd\"></a>May I print to the new Multi-Function Devices?</h2>\n<p><b>No</b>; they are not ready yet.</p>\n<p>ITS folks are researching for a centralized accounting system since May 2011; and before this new accounting system is in place, the MFDs are not capable of secured network printing.<br>\n</br></p>\n<p>We will keep everyone posted when the new accounting system in place.<br>\n</br></p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text \">\n<h2><a name=\"print-use-printcard\"></a>May I print to ITS printers using SFU printing cards?</h2>\n<p><b>Yes.</b></p>\n<h3>Burnaby campus</h3>\n<p>ITS provide printers, printing cards and release stations. The advantages include: you may get the printout when you are on the spot, and you could get the printouts at various locations all around campus.<br>\n</br></p>\n<p>From a FASnet Windows computer, please print to either <b>\\\\rcg-fs1.rcg.sfu.ca\\DCF_BnW</b> or <b>\\\\rcg-fs1.rcg.sfu.ca\\DCF_Color</b> and release it. Please note: these two printers are only available on rcg-fs1; and this is the only regualr use of rcg-fs1.<br>\n</br></p>\n<p>Please check <a href=\"/about/school-facilities/csil/how-to-print.html\">this page</a> for more details.<br>\n</br></p>\n<h3>Surrey campus</h3>\n<p>(to be answered)<br>\n</br></p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text \">\n<h2><a name=\"wireless-print\"></a>I\'m using a laptop, which printers I could use?</h2>\n<p>If you have a FASnet account, we recommend using a computer on FASnet or backbone to print.</p>\n<p>If you have to use the laptop print directly, please check out the <a href=\"#visitors\">previous Q&amp;A regarding visitors</a> for details.</p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text \">\n<hr>\n<h4>About using Konica/Minolta Multi-Function Devices</h4>\n</hr></div></div>\n<div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text \">\n<h2><a name=\"km-copy\"></a>How to make a copy</h2>\n<p>Please follow these steps:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Enter the user code; it is the same as you used on the old Toshiba photocopiers</li>\n<li>Click the \'login\' button on the touch screen</li>\n<li>Place the original in proper position</li>\n<li>When the light around the big \'start\' key is blue, it is ready to go</li>\n<li>Enter the number of copies, hit \'start\' Key</li>\n<li>Get all the copies, take out the original</li>\n<li>Hit the \'Access\' key to logout.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>You may further customize the photocopy feature.</p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text \">\n<h2><a name=\"km-scan\"></a>How to scan to an email account</h2>\n<p>The MFD could scan to a PDF file and email it to the user.</p>\n<p>Please follow these steps:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Enter the user code; it is the same as you used on the old Toshiba photocopiers</li>\n<li>Click the \'login\' button on the touch screen</li>\n<li>Place the original in proper position</li>\n<li>Hit the \'Scan\' key</li>\n<li>there are multiple ways to add recipient\'s email address<ul>\n<li>the \'address search\' feature looks up addresses in the SFU LDAP server; click \'ok\' to use the address<br>\n</br></li>\n<li>the \'direct input\' button lets you type an email address; click \'ok\' to use the address<br>\n</br></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Hit \'Start\' key - when the light around the big \'Start\' key is blue it is ready to scan<br>\n</br></li>\n<li>You may add more originals and click \'Start\' key for each page;</li>\n<li>Hit the \'Finish\' button on the touch screen and click \'Start\' key to send the email.</li>\n<li>Hit the \'Access\' key to logout.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>You may further customize the scan feature.<br>\n</br></p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text \">\n<h2><a name=\"km-transparency\"></a>How to photocopy to overhead transparencies</h2>\n<p>First, please make sure you are <b>using transparencies from a box labeled for use in printers/copiers</b>.<br>\n</br></p>\n<p>Now, please follow these steps:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Enter the user code; it is the same as you used on the old Toshiba photocopiers</li>\n<li>Click the \'login\' button on the touch screen</li>\n<li>Set original to single sided (- Basic tab / Duplex button / 1:1 setting, click \'OK\')</li>\n<li>Load a single transparency into <b>bypass tray</b></li>\n<li>A screen will appear, select transparency for paper type and confirm letter size, click \'OK\'</li>\n<li>When the light around the big \'start\' key is blue, it is ready to go</li>\n<li>Hit \'start\' Key to make one copy<br>\n</br></li>\n<li>Load one sheet of transparency at a time until the job is done.<br>\n</br></li>\n<li>Hit the \'Access\' key to logout.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><b>Warning</b>: Loading multiple sheets of transparency is not recommended, the sheets stick together too tight and may causes jams and/or melting.</p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text \">\n<hr>\n<h4>known issues<br>\n</br></h4>\n</hr></div></div>\n<div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text \">\n<h2><a name=\"issue-no-color\"></a>I don\'t get color printout while I print to a color printer; what I should do?<br>\n</br></h2>\n<p>For HP printers, this is a known issue with certain version of the Universal Printer Driver; it could not handle the color printing.</p>\n<p>The issue may be resolved by using the latest Universal Printer Driver from HP. Please remove the printer from the list and add it again, this will force the system use the new driver.</p>\n<p>For Windows systems, please always use the printers configured on \"<b>printserv1.fas.sfu.ca</b>\" to avoid this issue.<br>\n</br></p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text \">\n<h2><a name=\"issue-multi-page-per-sheet\"></a>I print multiple copies but only got one copy; what I should do?</h2>\n<p>For HP printers, this is a known issue on certain (type of) print servers.</p>\n<p>The workaround: please manually print multiple times for the same job.</p>\n<p>For Windows systems, please always use the printers configured on \"<b>printserv1.fas.sfu.ca</b>\" to avoid this issue.</p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text \">\n<h2><a name=\"issue-duplex\"></a>I print a single page, but it shows the job has 2 pages; what I should do?</h2>\n<p>The symptoms: when print odd number of pages, the print server always generates a job with even number of pages when the print is set to print \"double-sided\" or \"deplux\".</p>\n<p>For HP printers, this is a known issue on certain (type of) print servers.</p>\n<p>The workaround: you may change the printer to use single-sided finishing as a quick workaround.</p>\n<p>For a Windows system, please always use the printers configured on \"<b>printserv1.fas.sfu.ca</b>\" to avoid this issue.</p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text \">\n<h2><a name=\"issue-sims\"></a>I have trouble printing within SIMS; what I should do?</h2>\n<p>The symptoms: when print within SIMS, the printout does not reach expected result.</p>\n<p>Workaround #1 (verified at 2012.05.28): For Windows users, please follow these guide lines:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>please use IE (Internet Explorer) connect to SIMS</li>\n<li>please double-click within the area you would like to print<br>\n</br></li>\n<li>click menu <b>File</b> -&gt; <b>Print...</b></li>\n<li>select the desired printer (or pseudo/PDF printer)</li>\n<li>click tab \"<b>Options</b>\"<br>\n</br></li>\n<li>make sure \"<b>Only the selected frame</b>\" is selected</li>\n<li>click Print and keep your fingers crossed.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The tip: if there is a \"print friendly\" button or link on the page, always use it :)</p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text \">\n<h2><a name=\"issue-papersize\"></a>I print from a Windows computer but the printout is shifted somehow; what I should do?</h2>\n<p>This is a known issue when print to the samba print server \"rcg-fs1\" from a Windows computer; due to incorrect paper size for the print job.</p>\n<p>Technical description of the issue: although the printer configured on \"rcg-fs1\" is set to use \"letter\" as the default paper size, the client computer may interpret this value the wrong way. i.e. Windows XP may see it as 11x17.<br>\n</br></p>\n<p>We are still working on a fix, but here are some workarounds you may try:<br>\n</br></p>\n<p style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">Workaround #1: Use the print server <b>printserv1.fas.sfu.ca</b></p>\n<p style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">Workaround #2: Manually change the paper size of the printer to desired one - every time you print. Please note: only change the \"printer preferences\" won\'t work for most of the applications.</p>\n<p style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">Workaround #3: upgrade the computer OS to Windows 7.</p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text \">\n<h2><a name=\"issue-filesize\"></a>I scaned a lot of pages on the MFD and sent to my SFU Connect email address, but I did not get the scanned file nor got any error message; what happened?</h2>\n<p>The issue is: the scanned file is too big. The SFU Connect server rejected the huge attachment.</p>\n<p>The workaround: please always scan to smaller files. e.g. scan 20 pages or less to a file, send the email and then next 20 pages and so on.</p>\n<p>You may want to use \"Compact PDF\" document type for your scanning. This will generate PDF files in 1/4 of regular size. And you may also select 200dpi to futher reduce the file size. Please try out a few pages to see if the resulting file is satisfactory.</p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text \">\n<h2><a name=\"issue-sliceoff-mac\"></a>I print from a Mac computer but the printout is sliced-off somehow; what I should do?</h2>\n<p>This is a known issue. We are investigating.<br>\n</br></p>\n<p>Here is the workaround before a solution is found:</p>\n<p style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">Please print it</p>\n<ul>\n<li>with the \"Scale to Fit\" button selected, and</li>\n<li>with the \"Fill Entire Paper\" button selected.</li>\n</ul>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text \">\n<hr>\n<h4>Extras</h4>\n</hr></div></div>\n<div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text \">\n<h2>How to report issues regarding printer/photocopier?</h2>\n<p>Please <a href=\"/about/school-facilities/how-to-contact-helpdesk.html\">email helpdesk</a>.</p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text \">\n<h2>I got more questions; what I should do?</h2>\n<p>Please <a href=\"/about/school-facilities/how-to-contact-helpdesk.html\">email helpdesk</a> for more information.</p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text ruled\">\n<hr>\n<p>Last updated @ 2013.01.13</p>\n</hr></div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div id=\"sub_content_wrapper\">\n<div class=\"parsys aboveSubContent\"><div class=\"parbase section reference\"><div class=\"cq-dd-paragraph\"><div class=\"searchwidget\">\n<div class=\"\">\n<p>Search Computing Science</p>\n<form action=\"/search.html\" method=\"get\">\n<input name=\"q\" placeholder=\"\"/>\n<input class=\"submit\" type=\"submit\" value=\"Search\"/>\n</form>\n</div></div>\n</div></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"parsys sub_content\"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div id=\"footer\">\n<ul>\n<li>8888 University Drive, Burnaby, B.C. Canada V5A 1S6</li>\n<li><a href=\"//www.sfu.ca/webmaster/terms.html\">