eople/emeriti.html\">Emeriti Faculty Members</a></li><li><a href=\"/people/adjunct.html\">Adjunct Professors</a></li><li><a href=\"/people/associate.html\">Associate Members</a></li><li class=\"over\"><a href=\"/people/ebco-epic-visiting-chairs.html\">Ebco/Epic Visiting Chairs</a></li><li><a href=\"/people/graduate.html\">Graduate Students</a></li><li><a href=\"/people/staff.html\">Staff</a></li><li><a href=\"/people/exceptional-alumni.html\">Exceptional Alumni</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li><li><a href=\"/newsandevents.html\">News &amp; Events</a></li><li class=\"rule\">Â </li><li><a href=\"https://intraweb.cs.sfu.ca/\">Intranet</a></li><li><a href=\"https://portal.cs.sfu.ca/\">Portal</a></li>\n</ul><ul><li class=\"rule\">Â </li></ul><div class=\"parsys contentBelow\"><div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text \">\n<p>Â  FOLLOW AND SHARE</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.facebook.com/FAS.SFU\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"/content/dam/sfu/images/icons/facebook_32.png\"/></a> <a href=\"https://twitter.com/#!/FAS_SFU\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"/content/dam/sfu/images/icons/twitter_32.png\"/></a> <a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/fas_sfu\" target=\"_blank\"><img height=\"35\" src=\"/content/dam/sfu/images/icons/flickr.png\" width=\"35\"/></a> <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/fascomms\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"/content/dam/sfu/images/icons/youtube-icon_32x32.png\"/></a></p>\n</div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div id=\"content_2col\">\n<div class=\"breadcrumb\">\n<a href=\"/computing.html\">Computing Science</a>Â &gt;Â <a href=\"/people.html\">People</a>Â &gt;Â <a href=\"/people/ebco-epic-visiting-chairs.html\">Ebco/Epic Visiting Chairs</a></div>\n<div id=\"main_content_wrapper\">\n<div class=\"parsys main_content\"><div class=\"title section\"><div><h1>Ebco/Epic Visiting Chairs</h1></div></div>\n<div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text \">\n<p>The School of Computing Science is committed to maintaining a top-ranked research environment, and such an environment requires new ideas, people, and connections to other universities worldwide. The Ebco/Epic Visiting Chairs program supports the School of Computing Science in hosting many scientists of national and international prominence. The program is funded by an endowment from Hugo and Helmut Eppich. The Ebco/Epic endowment is leveraged with research funds from an SFU faculty host and support that the Visitors receive from their home institutions to offer attractive conditions for top-quality outside researchers. The visiting researchers stay for a least a month to collaborate with SFU faculty and students. Each visitor gives a lecture as part of the Ebco/Epic seminar series that brings cutting-edge ideas in computer science to SFU. </p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"text parbase section\">\n<div class=\"text \">\n<h2><b>2010</b></h2>\n<p><b>Tamaki, Hisao</b></p>\n<p><b>Title:</b> Visiting Scholar <b>Home Institution:</b> Meiji University</p>\n<p><b>Area:</b> Algorithmic Graph Theory.</p>\n<p><b>Dates of Visit:</b> August 24 â€“ September 23, 2010<b>Hosts:</b> <a href=\"http://www2.cs.sfu.ca/people/Faculty/Profile/qgu.html\">Gu, Qianping</a></p>\n<p><b>SFU Location:</b> <b>Contact Information:</b> tamaki@cs.meiji.ac.jp</p>\n<p><b>Ebco/Epic Seminar Title:</b> Not Available</p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p><b>Chen, Min</b></p>\n<p><b>Title:</b> Visiting Scholar <b>Home Institution:</b> Seoul National University, South Korea</p>\n<p><b>Area:</b> Wireless Sensor Networks &amp; Ubiquitous Computing.</p>\n<p><b>Dates of Visit:</b> August 1, 2010 - August 31, 2010<b>Hosts:</b> <a href=\"http://www2.cs.sfu.ca/people/Faculty/Profile/jcliu.html\">Liu, Jiangchuan</a></p>\n<p><b>SFU Location:</b> <b>Contact Information:</b> minchen@ieee.org</p>\n<p><b>Ebco/Epic Seminar Title:</b> Mobile Agent Based Ubiquitous Networks and Services</p>\n<p><b>Â </b></p>\n<p><b>Wang, Qixin</b></p>\n<p><b>Title:</b> Visiting Scholar <b>Home Institution:</b> Polytechnic University, Hong Kong</