t_menu_links\" href=\"http://www.sfu.ca/applicantundergrads/\">Apply: Undergraduate</a> </li>\n<li class=\"\"><a class=\"left_menu_links\" href=\"http://www.cs.sfu.ca/gradpgm/Apply/\">Apply: Graduate</a></li>\n<li class=\" dotted\"><a class=\"left_menu_links\" href=\"http://calendar.cs.sfu.ca\">Calendar</a></li>\n<li class=\"\"><a class=\"left_menu_links\" href=\"http://www.cs.sfu.ca/CC/adbooking/index1.cgi\">Advisor Booking</a></li>\n<li class=\" dotted\"><a class=\"left_menu_links\" href=\"/outlines/\">Course Outlines</a></li>\n</ul>\n</div> <!-- flymenu div -->\n</div> <!-- close left_col_container -->\n<div id=\"right_col_container_with_lhs_menu\" style=\"margin-bottom:0; margin-top:0; padding-bottom:0; padding-top:0; \">\n<!-- This is where I\'d like to add the bread crumbs text -->\n<div id=\"sysmenu\">\n<a href=\"/portal/login/\">Login</a>\n</div>\n<div id=\"breadcrumbs\">\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.cs.sfu.ca/\">CS SFU</a></li><li>&gt; <a href=\"/portal/\">Portal</a></li> <li>&gt; <a href=\"/portal/outlines/\">Outlines</a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div id=\"AppTitle\"> Computing Science Course Outlines </div>\n<div id=\"main\">\n<br/>\n<div align=\"right\" style=\"margin-right: 10px;\">\n<a href=\"/portal/outlines/1134-CMPT-466-D100/pdf\">\n<img class=\"help\" height=\"30px\" src=\"/media/images/pdfIcon.jpg\" style=\"border: 0px none ;\" title=\"Download a PDF version of CMPT 466\'s outline\" width=\"30px\"/></a></div>\n<h1 id=\"PageTitle\">Course Outline - CMPT 466 - Animation</h1>\n<h2 class=\"ParagraphTitle\">Information</h2>\n<div>\n<div style=\"float:left; width:200px;\">\n<p style=\"padding-bottom:.5em;\">Subject</p>\n<p style=\"padding-bottom:.5em;\">Catalog Number</p>\n<p style=\"padding-bottom:.5em;\">Section</p>\n<p style=\"padding-bottom:.5em;\">Semester</p>\n<p style=\"padding-bottom:.5em;\">Title</p>\n<p style=\"padding-bottom:.5em;\">Instructor(s)</p>\n<p style=\"padding-bottom:.5em;\">Campus</p>\n</div>\n<div style=\"padding-left:20px;\">\n<p style=\"padding-bottom:.5em;\">CMPT</p>\n<p style=\"padding-bottom:.5em;\">466</p>\n<p style=\"padding-bottom:.5em;\">D100</p>\n<p style=\"padding-bottom:.5em;\">2013 Summer (1134)</p>\n<p style=\"padding-bottom:.5em;\">Animation</p>\n<p style=\"padding-bottom:.5em;\">\n                    Richard Zhang Â Â \n                \n			</p>\n<p style=\"padding-bottom:5px;\">Burnaby Mountain Campus</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<h2 class=\"ParagraphTitle\">Calendar Objective/Description</h2>\n<p>Topics and techniques in animation, including: The history of animation, computers in animation, traditional animation approaches, and computer animation techniques such as geometric modelling, interpolation, camera controls, kinematics, dynamics, constraint-based animation, realistic motion, temporal aliasing, digital effects and post production. </p>\n<h2 class=\"ParagraphTitle\">Instructor\'s Objectives</h2>\n<p style=\"LastSection\">The course is intended to be a hands-on introduction to the field of\r\ncomputer animation.  Students will be provided with software to create\r\ntheir own animations (although computing science students may wish to\r\ndevelop animation software).  The idea is to create a course that can be\r\ntaken by computer scientists and artists (or other those in any other\r\ndiscipline) alike.</p>\n<h2 class=\"ParagraphTitle\">Prerequisites</h2>\n<p style=\"LastSection\"> CMPT 361 and MACM 316 or permission of the instructor.</p>\n<h2 class=\"ParagraphTitle\">Topics</h2>\n<ul> <li>Historical perspective of computer animation.</li>\n<li>Mastery of basic techniques to interpolate the movement of objects,  forward and inverse kinematics</li>\n<li>Familiarity with physically based animation, energy minimization, and constraint-based animation</li></ul>\n<h2 class=\"ParagraphTitle\">Grading</h2>\n<p>      To be announced during the first week of classes.\r\n</p>\n<p style=\"LastSection\">Students must attain an overall passing \n        grade on the weighted average of exams in the course in order to \n        obtain a clear pass (C- or better).</p>\n<h2 class=\"ParagraphTitle\">Required Books</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Computer Animation - Algorithms and Techniques , Rick Parent, Morgan Kaufmann, 2012, 9780124158429, 3rd Edition </li>\n</ul>\n<h2 class=\"ParagraphTitle\">Reference Books</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>The Animation Book, Kit Laybourne, Crown Publishing/Three Rivers Press, 1998, 9780517886021 </li>\n<li>The Animator\'s Workbook, Tony White, Watson-Guptill, 1988, 9780823002290 </li>\n</ul>\n<h2 class=\"ParagraphTitle\">Academic Honesty Statement</h2>\n<p>Academic honesty plays a key role in our efforts to maintain a high standard of academic excellence and integrity. Students are advised that ALL acts of intellectual dishonesty will be handled in accordance with the SFU Academic Honesty and Student Conduct Policies ( http://www.sfu.ca/policies/gazette/student.html ).</p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"last_updated_block\"> Data Last Updated:  </div>\n</div>\n<div>\n    Â \n</div>\n<div style=\"clear:both; \"></div>\n</div> <!-- end the two_col_container  -->\n<!-- The following code is for the SFU grey footer bar  -->\n<div id=\"footer\">\n\n            8888 University Drive, Burnaby, B.C. Canada V5A 1S6 |\n            <a href=\"http://www.sfu.ca/webmaster/terms.html\">Terms / Privacy</a> |\n            <a href=\"http://www.cs.sfu.ca/AboutCMPT/contacts.html\">Contact CS</a> |\n            <a href=\"mailto:helpdesk@cs.sfu.ca?subject=Website%20User%20Feedback&amp;body=The%20page%20you%20are%20submitting%20feedback%20from%20is: /\">Webmaster</a> |\n            <a href=\"http://www.cs.sfu.ca/sitemap.html\">SiteMap</a> |\n            <a href=\"http://www.sfu.ca/security/sfuroadconditions/\">Road Conditions</a> |\n            Â© Simon Fraser University\n        </div>\n</div> <!-- Close the \"container\" div -->\n <!-- Close the \"container\" div -->\n</body>\n</html>\n','2013-04-01 03:03:42.254858'),('https://portal.cs.sfu.ca/portal/outlines/1134-CMPT-477-D1