:200px;\">\n<p style=\"padding-bottom:.5em;\">Subject</p>\n<p style=\"padding-bottom:.5em;\">Catalog Number</p>\n<p style=\"padding-bottom:.5em;\">Section</p>\n<p style=\"padding-bottom:.5em;\">Semester</p>\n<p style=\"padding-bottom:.5em;\">Title</p>\n<p style=\"padding-bottom:.5em;\">Instructor(s)</p>\n<p style=\"padding-bottom:.5em;\">Campus</p>\n</div>\n<div style=\"padding-left:20px;\">\n<p style=\"padding-bottom:.5em;\">CMPT</p>\n<p style=\"padding-bottom:.5em;\">705</p>\n<p style=\"padding-bottom:.5em;\">G100</p>\n<p style=\"padding-bottom:.5em;\">2013 Summer (1134)</p>\n<p style=\"padding-bottom:.5em;\">Design and Analysis of Algorithms</p>\n<p style=\"padding-bottom:.5em;\">\n                    Petra Berenbrink Â Â \n                \n			</p>\n<p style=\"padding-bottom:5px;\">Burnaby Mountain Campus</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<h2 class=\"ParagraphTitle\">Calendar Objective/Description</h2>\n<p>The objective of this course is to expose students to basic techniques in algorithm design and analysis. Topics will include greedy algorithms, dynamic programming, advanced data structures, network flows, randomized algorithms.</p>\n<h2 class=\"ParagraphTitle\">Instructor\'s Objectives</h2>\n<p style=\"LastSection\">In this first part of the class we will cover programming paradigms like greedy and dynamic programming. Then we will gave a look at classical graph algorithms. For the last part of the class the students have the choice between randomized algorithms, mathematical algorithms, parallel algorithms, game theory,  and linear programming.</p>\n<h2 class=\"ParagraphTitle\">Prerequisites</h2>\n<p style=\"LastSection\">None</p>\n<h2 class=\"ParagraphTitle\">Topics</h2>\n<ul> <li>Review of Models of Computation</li>\n<li>Dynamic Programming</li>\n<li>Greedy Algorithms</li>\n<li>Graph Algorithms</li>\n<li>Network Flow</li>\n<li>NP-Completeness</li>\n<li>Approximation Algorithms</li>\n<li>Random Algorithms</li>\n<li>Game Theory</li></ul>\n<h2 class=\"ParagraphTitle\">Grading</h2>\n<p>       Grading will be confirmed the first week of classes.</p>\n<h2 class=\"ParagraphTitle\">Required Books</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Introduction to Algorithms, Cormen,  Leiserson,  Rivest,  Stein, MIT Press, 2009,  9780262033848, 3rd Edition </li>\n<li>Randomized Algorithms, Motwani and Raghavan, Cambridge University Press, 1995,  9780521474658, 1st </li>\n</ul>\n<h2 class=\"ParagraphTitle\">Academic Honesty Statement</h2>\n<p>Academic honesty plays a key role in our efforts to maintain a high standard of academic excellence and integrity. Students are advised that ALL acts of intellectual dishonesty will be handled in accordance with the SFU Academic Honesty and Student Conduct Policies ( http://www.sfu.ca/policies/gazette/student.html ).</p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"last_updated_block\"> Data Last Updated:  </div>\n</div>\n<div>\n    Â \n</div>\n<div style=\"clear:both; \"></div>\n</div> <!-- end the two_col_container  -->\n<!-- The following code is for the SFU grey footer bar  -->\n<div id=\"footer\">\n\n            8888 University Drive, Burnaby, B.C. Canada V5A 1S6 |\n            <a href=\"http://www.sfu.ca/webmaster/terms.html\">Terms / Privacy</a> |\n            <a href=\"http://www.cs.sfu.ca/AboutCMPT/contacts.html\">Contact CS</a> |\n            <a href=\"mailto:helpdesk@cs.sfu.ca?subject=Website%20User%20Feedback&amp;body=The%20page%20you%20are%20submitting%20feedback%20from%20is: /\">Webmaster</a> |\n            <a href=\"http://www.cs.sfu.ca/sitemap.html\">SiteMap</a> |\n            <a href=\"http://www.sfu.ca/security/sfuroadconditions/\">Road Conditions</a> |\n            Â© Simon Fraser University\n        </div>\n</div> <!-- Close the \"container\" div -->\n <!-- Close the \"container\" div -->\n</body>\n</html>\n','2013-04-01 03:02:34.225838'),('https://portal.cs.sfu.ca/portal/outlines/1134-CMPT-777-G100/','SFU Computing Science Course Outlines','\n<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC \"-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN\" \"http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DT